<div class='panel panel-default'>
  <div class="panel-heading">Search tips</div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <ul class="advanced-help">

      <li>Select <strong>match all</strong> to require all fields (e.g. Title AND Author).
     </li>

     <li>Select <strong>match any</strong> to find at least one field (e.g. Title OR Subject).
     </li>

     <li>Combine keywords and attributes to find specific items.
     </li>

     <li>Use <strong>quotation</strong> marks to search as a <strong>phrase</strong>. 
     
       <li>Use <strong>+</strong> before a term to make it <strong>required</strong>.</li>
     
       <li>Use <strong>-</strong> before a word or phrase to <strong>exclude</strong>. 

         <li>Use "OR", "AND", and "NOT" (uppercase) to create <strong>Boolean</strong> logic within a field. You can use parentheses in your complex expressions. </li>
     <li>Truncation and wildcards are not supported - word-stemming is done automatically.</li>
   </ul>
  </div>
</div>
